<HEADLINE> China Wants ESCAP to Narrow Development Gap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The major objective of the
cooperation within the Economic and Social Commission for Asia and
the Pacific (ESCAP) should be to narrow the gap in development
between the developed and the developing members, a Chinese
delegate said here today.
</P>
<P>
Great gaps among ESCAP members in the economic development
level are the most salient problem in the region and cooperation
within ESCAP should be targeted at the problem, said Chinese
Assistant Foreign Minister Yang Wenchang.
</P>
<P>
The funding for major ESCAP cooperation projects should have
priorities, said the head of the Chinese delegation at the opening
of the ministerial segment of ESCAP's 53rd session.
</P>
<P>
He proposed that cooperation in science and technology, poverty
eradication, environment protection, human resource development
and infrastructure construction should be areas of priority.
</P>
<P>
Yang also said that the cooperation within ESCAP needs
institutional and funds guarantees.
</P>
<P>
Every key project should have its own special committee to
supervise its planning and implementation and examine the result,
yang said.
</P>
<P>
All ESCAP members should make their own contributions in
accordance with their abilities, he said, but calling on developed
members to shoulder more responsibilities in financial assistance,
technology transfer and opening of their markets.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese delegate proposed that ESCAP start to consider the
drafting of agenda 21 (ESCAP) to chart the direction of the
development and cooperation for the region in the new century.
</P>
<P>
As one of the founding members of ESCAP, Yang said, China has
all along attached importance to cooperation with other ESCAP
members and supported ESCAP's operations.
</P>
<P>
ESCAP has rendered useful help to China's economic development
and its reform and opening up, he said. China will, as it used to,
maintain and develop friendly relations and cooperation with
ESCAP.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government and people stand ready to make joint
efforts with other countries in the region to bring a prosperous
and developed Asia-Pacific region with long-standing peace and
stability into the 21st century.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
