<HEADLINE> Pak Women Urged to Cast off Self-negating Attitude </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Minister for
Population Welfare Syeda Abida Hussain today called upon young
women to cast off their self-effacing posture and achieve
awareness of their rights.
</P>
<P>
"The woman will have to change their self-negating attitude and
achieve self-realization that they are as important as men and
have to play equally important role in our social as well as
national life," Abida was quoted as saying by the Associated Press
of Pakistan at a meeting here today.
</P>
<P>
She said a country cannot progress if half of its human
resources languish.
</P>
<P>
"You have to recognize your potential that will be vital for
country's progress," she said.
</P>
<P>
"At the same time you should be aware of your duties, we are
the seventh largest population of the world but are at a poor
132nd in economic progress, we will have to check our alarming
population rate for sustainable progress," she said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
