<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen Arrives in Washington for Talks with </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 28 (Xinhua) -- China's Vice-Premier and
foreign Minister Qian Qichen arrived in Washington on Monday
morning for talks with U.S. leaders on bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Qian Qichen is going to meet U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine
Albright this afternoon at the State Department and is expected to
meet President Bill Clinton before leaving on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Their talks are expected to focus on the arrangement for a
summit between Chinese President Jiang Zeming and U.S. President
Clinton as scheduled this fall.
</P>
<P>
Other issues about bilateral and Asia-Pacific regional
interests are also expected to be on agenda when Qian Qichen
holds talks with Clinton and Albright. 
</P>
</TEXT>
