<HEADLINE> Angola's Food Security Situation Serious </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, APRIL 28 (Xinhua) -- Angola's food security
situation is serious, said Agriculture Minister Carlos
Fernandes here today.
</P>
<P>
About 60 percent of the Angolan people are living under the
poverty line, the minister said at a press conference on the
symposium of agriculture restoration and development to be held
here on May 6-8.
</P>
<P>
If Angola wants to realize the goal for its restoration and
reconstruction, the country's agriculture must develop as rapidly
as possible, he said.
</P>
<P>
However, he pointed out that the Angolan government has no
enough money for the development of agriculture. "Such a
situation must be changed by encouraging privote investment," he
added.
</P>
<P>
According to the minister, participants of the symposium
will discuss ways for the agricultural growth, and formulate
policies and strategies for this purpose. enditem


