<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 120 Teams Confirm for World Taekwondo in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Some 120 teams all around the
world have confirm their entries to the 1997 World Taekwondo
Championships this fall in Hong Kong, the Organizers said here on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The November 18-23 event slated for the Hong Kong Coliseum in
Kowloon is the 13th men's world championships and the sixth
version for the women.
</P>
<P>
This would be the first world-class sporting event to be hosted
by Hong Kong after its handover at midnight on June 30 this year.
</P>
<P>
And Hong Kong will participate in the world championships by
adopting the name of "Hong Kong, China" for the first time, Ching
Men Ky, President of the Hong Kong Taekwondo Association, had said
early this year.
</P>
<P>
Invitations had been sent to over 150 member associations of
the World Taekwondo Federation (WTF), the sport's world governing
body, and some 1,000 participants are expected at the event,
according to Organizers.
</P>
<P>
This is the third Asian country or region to host the biennial
event, following South Korea and the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
The total cost for hosting the championships is estimated as
1.66 million U.S. dollars, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
WTF Vice-President Ching Woo Lee of South Korea said he was
satisfied with the championship venue and was happy for the
progress the Organizing Committee had so far achieved. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
