<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Urges to Enhance World Cooperation on Human </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice Minister for
Construction Li Zhendong called here today for further world
cooperation on sustainable human settlements development and
implementation of the Habitat Agenda made in Istanbul in 1996.
</P>
<P>
"The promotion of human settlements development by taking
effective measures... is a common historic task facing all of
us," he said at the 16th session of the U.N. Commission for Human
Settlements which opened today.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. should play a significant role in the field, he
noted, urging the international community to carry out its
commitment and create favorable conditions for the developing
countries to improve their people's living conditions.
</P>
<P>
Soon after the Istanbul Habitat Two Conference, the Chinese
government decided to speed up the housing construction for the
ordinary Chinese people, seeing it as part of the national
development strategy up to 2010, said Li.
</P>
<P>
China has been prepared to build 11 billion square meters of
new housing in the next 15 years, he announced.
</P>
<P>
China has also intensified its efforts to transform the
existing housing system to a market-oriented system, raised the
proportion of commercialized housing and spread Central
Provident Fund for housing so as to reach the goal, he said.
</P>
<P>
China holds "the policy that equal attention should be paid to
both saving and developing resources" when developing
settlements, he concluded at the U.N. meeting on human
settlements, which will end on May 7. enditem

