<HEADLINE> Lesotho Praised for Helping S. African Freedom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 28 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's High
Commissioner to Lesotho Japhet Ndlovu today praised Lesotho for
its assistance to S. African freedom fighters during the
apartheid era.
</P>
<P>
A report by the South African Press Association from Maseru,
the capital of Lesotho, said that the mountain kingdom offered
political asylum to hundreds of members of South African
liberation movements during the period.
</P>
<P>
Many Lasotho people "were witnesses to the historical
developments that took place during the struggle for the
dismantling of apartheid", said Ndlovu at a function in Maseru to
mark South Africa's third National Freedom Day on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
On the bilateral relations between the two countries, Ndlovu
said the two governments had tackled important issues together,
citing the study permits for Lasotho students in South Africa
and the cross border shooting.
</P>
<P>
The border problems had been brought under control through
district liaison committees which tackled a wide range of
problems affecting communities on both sides of the border, added
Ndlovu. enditem

