<HEADLINE> British Government to Send Troops to Zaire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The British government is to send
some 200 British troops to Zaire as an additional precautious
measure in case of evacuating British and Commonwealth nationals
from the African nation.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the British Ministry of Defense was quoted by
the Reuters news agency as saying this afternoon: "There is no
need as yet to evacuate British nationals. We are taking
additional precautions putting troops closer to hand in case they
should be needed."
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that the British troops, which would leave
over the next few days, would fly to Libreville in Gabon and 38
British Royal Marines were already in Brazzaville in the Congo
ready to evacuate British nationals from the Zairean capital
Kinshasa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
