<HEADLINE> East African Leaders Ready for Summit on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian President
Benjamin Mkapa and his Kenyan counterpart Daniel arap Moi arrived
at the northern Tanzanian town of Arusha today, ready for
tomorrow's second summit of the three-member East Africa
Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
A report reaching here said that Ugandan President Yoweri
Museveni is expected in Arusha tomorrow morning to attend the
summit of the EAC set up in March last year.
</P>
<P>
Moi, also the current summit chairman, toured the EAC
Secretariat offices in Arusha later today.
</P>
<P>
He was briefed on various issues on regional cooperation by
the secretariat top executive and other officials.
</P>
<P>
The EAC leaders were expected to launch the East African
Development Strategy, a four-year comprehensive action plan aimed
at guiding the integration process between 1997-2000, at the
one-day summit.
</P>
<P>
They will then launch the east African passports so as to help
cross-border movements of people in the region.
</P>
<P>
The passport, which has a blue cover with the coat of arms of
the issuing state on the front cover and that of the EAC on the
back cover, will be strictly used in the East Africa region.
</P>
<P>
Then there will be hoisting of the east African flag by the
three presidents, a flag which incorporates most of the colors of
the national flags of the member states.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation flag has a blue background, signifying the
blue water of Lake Victoria. There is a handshake below the EAC
coat of arms which signifies the amity of the people of east
Africa.
</P>
<P>
It was not immediately known where the flags will be hoisted
besides the EAC headquarters in Arusha. As many as 420 standard,
car and desk flags have been made in South Africa, costing 5,500
U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the EAC said all diplomatic missions accredited
to the three countries and other regional leaders have been
invited to attend tomorrow's function.
</P>
<P>
The presidents are expected to leave for home later in the
day. enditem

