<HEADLINE> Over 200 Observers to Supervise Legislative </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Algerian Prime Minister Ahmed
Ouyahia disclosed today that more than 200 foreign observers will
arrive in Algeria to supervise the legislative elections due to
take place on June 5.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a news conference here, the prime minister said the
Arab League will send 60 observers early May and the Organization
of African Unity (OAU) will send 60 to 70 observers to supervise
the legislative elections.
</P>
<P>
As to the United Nations, he said, 19 out of the 42 countries
which have been invited to send observers to Algeria, have
favorably responded to Algeria's request.
</P>
<P>
Altogether, he indicated, some 100 observers will be dispatched
by the U.N. to Algeria at the appropriate time.
</P>
<P>
The upcoming elections in Algeria are considered an important
and decisive step aimed at achieving stability in the country.
Most opposition parties intend to contest the elections.
</P>
<P>
There are so far 73 opposition political parties in Algeria.
</P>
