<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Improves Telephone Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's Posts and
Telecommunications Corporation (PTC) is conducting a program
worth 90.91 million U.S. Dollars in a bid to better the national
telephone network and thus help the country get more investment.
</P>
<P>
The Zimbabwe Investment Center today said the PTC's capital
budget, submitted to the parliament recently, showed that the
bulk of the investment would be incurred on the ongoing
digitalization program and on upgrading the existing network.
</P>
<P>
"Most of the funds to finance the projects would be raised
from the PTC's own resources as well as donors," said the center.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank warned last year that the country's
telecommunications network could be a deterrent to investment.
</P>
<P>
The PTC has more than 100,000 potential subscribers awaiting a
telephone line. enditem

