<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Beats Kyrgyzstan at Asian Women's Basketball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Defending Champions China scored
their second win in as many outings Monday after beating
Kyrgyzstan 100-61 in group A at the 17th Asian Women's Basketball
Championship.
</P>
<P>
It was an easy win for the defending champions when 2.04-meter
taller center Zheng Haixia led her teammates to a 55-30 lop-sided
leading at the end of the first half.
</P>
<P>
In other group A games on Monday, South Korea edged Japan 73-71
after blowing a 44-34 lead at the interval.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Taipei defeated Thailand 100-4 also in group A.
</P>
<P>
In two group B games, Kazakhstan downed Singapore 87-36 and
Hong Kong outlasted Macao 86-32.
</P>
<P>
The championship are divided into two groups of round-robin
contests. The top four finishers in group A qualify for the
semifinals while the sixth and last team dropped into the lower
class group B for next championships.
</P>
<P>
The top team from the group B will upgraded to group A. Other
teams in group B are Malaysia, Indonesia, and India.
</P>
<P>
The final top three team of group A will represent Asia in the
1998 women's world basketball championships in Germany. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
