<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-28 17:52 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 237 Registered for Presidential Race in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Iran's Interior Ministry
announced here tonight that a total of 237 persons were
registered as applicants for the 7th presidential elections
scheduled for May 23.
</P>
<P>
The state-run Tehran Radio reported that the Guardian
Council, a supreme body above the Parliament, is to scrutinize
the qualifications of the applicants in 10 days.
</P>
<P>
However, the report gave no names of the specific applicants.
</P>
<P>
Observers here noted that the number of the applicants this
year is 185 percent higher than that of the previous
presidential elections four years ago.
</P>
<P>
It shows that more people are interested in the presidential
race since supreme leader Ali Khamenei and current President
Akbar Hashemi Rafsanjani will stay away from the race.
</P>
<P>
Iran's Constitution bars Rafsanjani from running for the
third term of the presidency. So he has to step down from the
office in August.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that Parliament Speaker Ali Akbar Nateq-Nouri,
former minister of culture and Islamic guidance Mohammad
Khatami, former minister of information Mohammad Mohammadi
Reyshahri and deputy head of the judiciary Seyed Reza Zavarei
are among the applicants.
</P>
<P>
The candidates have 12 days to run for the presidential race.
</P>
<P>
Actually, the 7th presidential election campaign has been
already in full swing across Iran since there are only 24 days
left to the elections.
</P>
<P>
Experts hold that more serious election activities are
expected in the coming days when the Guardian Council is to
issue its ruling on the nomination papers.
</P>
<P>
Observers said that the 54-year-old parliament speaker is the
front-runner who has a big chance of winning the presidential
race.
</P>
<P>
However, some political analysts said that the mild and open
personality of Mohammad Khatami is attracting more and more
support from the public, especially the educated people.
</P>
<P>
There will be a fierce battle between the two clergymen.
</P>
<P>
The next president will hold office in August. 
</P>
</TEXT>
