<HEADLINE> Africa Should Not Depend on Outside World for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Salim A Salim, Secretary
General of the Organization of African Unity (OAU), today stressed
that ''Africa should not depend on the outside world for survival
but should assume leadership on its own affairs.''
</P>
<P>
According to an OAU press release, Salim made the remaks
when he was meeting here a 10-member portfolio committee on
foreign affairs of the South African parliament.
</P>
<P>
Salim said the OAU agenda has now significantly shifted from
political affairs to socio-economic matters, through the establish-
ment of the African economic community.
</P>
<P>
Salim also elaborated on the issue of human rights and
democratization in Africa as being of major concern to the OAU.
</P>
<P>
On the Zaire crisis, he said the situation in Zaire was most
worrying.
</P>
<P>
He commended the role the South African government is playing
in bringing about an atmosphere of reconciliation in that
country. enditem

