<HEADLINE> OAU Calls for Immediate Talks to End War in Zaire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Salim Ahmed Salim, Secretary
General of the Organization of African Unity (OAU), today called
on the warring parties in Zaire to hold immediate talks seeking a
lasting and peaceful solution to the crisis in the country.
</P>
<P>
This will pave "the way to a peaceful transition leading to
general elections and new political dispensation in Zaire," he
said in a statement issued here.
</P>
<P>
He urged the parties concerned to take full advantage of the
on-going efforts by African leaders and by the UN/OAU special
representative for the Great Lakes region aimed at facilitating a
meeting between Zariean President Mobutu Sese Seko and Zairean
rebel leader Laurent Kabila.
</P>
<P>
He expressed concern over the deteriorating situation on
refugees and displaced people in eastern Zaire, saying that "I am
particularly disturbed by the most recent reports regarding
killings of Rwandan refugees in eastern Zaire."
</P>
<P>
Thousands of refugees particularly women and children are in
critical condition and need immediate access to humanitarian
assistance, he said.
</P>
<P>
Salim urged the parties concerned to cooperate with U.N.
agencies and other humanitarian institutions in providing
assistance to the refugees and facilitating their safe
repatriation. enditem

