<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-28 18:55 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egypt's Money Market to Reach Top Notch: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 28 (Xinhua) -- An expected increase in the
capital traded in the Egyptian money market will make it the
biggest market in the region, Egypt's top banking official
predicted today.
</P>
<P>
Mahmoud Abdel Aziz, board chairman of the Egyptian National
Bank, said the Israeli stock exchange now ranks first with a
market capital of 21 billion U.S. dollars, followed by the Saudi
market with 18 billion dollars and the Egyptian one with 12
billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Aziz said several favorable developments in the Egyptian money
market have contributed to its solidity and fortification both
domestically and internationally.
</P>
<P>
These include computerized systems on capital and share
trading as well as regular and daily data-circulation, said Aziz
who is also head of the Egyptian Banks Federation (EBF).
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian money market is also being linked to the largest
telecommunications networks the world over, he added.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, Egypt has signed cooperation
agreements with Bahrain and Jordan for the exchange of the
registration of their joint-stock companies and facilitating
dealings between the citizens of these countries.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the banking system's role in attracting foreign
capital, the volume of trading on the Egyptian Stock Exchange
(ESE) has largely increased, contributing to the marked progress
in implementing the privatization program, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, foreigners' demand on the bills, bonds and
securities graded in the ESE is on the rise and their
contribution to the total market value of traded securities
reached 31 percent, Aziz added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
