<HEADLINE> Annan to Visit China, Japan, Russia and Australia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 28 (Xinhua) -- UN Secretary-General Kofi
Annan will pay an official visit to China, Japan, Russia and
Australia in May, a UN spokesman announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Fred Eckhard, spokesman for the UN Secretary-General, said that
Annan will go to the Hague to participate in the first conference
of the state parties to the convention on banning chemical weapons
from May 5 to 6 and then go to China for an official visit from
May 7 to 11.
</P>
<P>
Then, he will visit Japan from May 11 to 14, Moscow from May 14
to 18 and Australia from May 18 to 21.
</P>
<P>
This is the Secretary-General's first official visit to the
four countries since he took office at the beginning of this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
