<HEADLINE> Mayor Escapes Armed Attack in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Baskale Mayor and Serefhan
tribe leader Iskender Ertus escaped unscathed an attack today as a
group of unidentified gunmen opened fire at him in Van province,
but five others were injured.
</P>
<P>
The gunmen jumped out of a car and attacked Ertus and his six
bodyguards with automatic weapons near Research Hospital of 100th
Year University in Van province at 17:20 local time (14:20 GMT),
the semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Ertus' bodyguards immediately responded and the gunmen escaped
by taking on waiting cars nearby.
</P>
<P>
Ertus was saved unscathed, but his two nieces, two Iranian
citizens and one student were injured, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that the injured had been taken to Van State
Hospital and the Research Hospital for treatment, adding that the
injured student, Nazli Berkler, was in serious conditions.
</P>
<P>
Turkish security teams had started operations to capture the
gunmen in the region, said the agency. 
</P>
