<HEADLINE> US Computer Giant Introduces First Home PC Theater </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The Compaq Computer Corporation,
the computer giant in the United States, introduced today its
first home personal computer theater that combines a fully
featured computer with a large-screen television.
</P>
<P>
The new device is put into the market at a time when the
nation's transition to digital television is about to appear next
year.
</P>
<P>
The PC theaters are considered large-screen entertainment
centers that double as computers, allowing consumers to watch
television programs or prerecorded movies, cruise the internet,
play computer games or send and receive E-mail.
</P>
<P>
With this product, the computer industry believes that it can
push its way into the television market because digital television
will be computer, in essence. The new PC theater was designed to
look like a television first and computer second.
</P>
<P>
Compaq says that the new product is primarily intended to prime
the market for the true digital television. The company felt
strongly that this was the direction it needed to go. 
</P>
