<HEADLINE> Donors Conference on Bosnia to Be Held in Late May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO, April 28 (Xinhua) -- A long-delayed international
conference to assist the Bosnian reconstruction will be held in
May 25, the Sarajevo daily "Oslobodjenje" reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The date was confirmed by Nedeljko Despotovic, a senior
official of the Bosnian Federation which, he said, had been
formally notified by the organizers.
</P>
<P>
The so-called donors conference, during which more than 1.4
billion dollars are expected to be pledged, had been postponed
several times because the Bosnian parties failed to fulfill
conditions set by the Office of High Representative, which is in
charge of the Dayton accords implementation.
</P>
<P>
The conference was conditioned on the passage of an economic
package which include bills on central bank, currency, customs,
payment of debt, tariff and foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
Although most items of the package are still unsettled, West
European countries and the United States, who are the major
donors, seem to be resigned fearful that further delaying the
conference would not result in real progress in the peace process.
</P>
</TEXT>
