<HEADLINE> Senior Communist Party Official Hu Jintao Hails Labor Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese Communist Party
official extended greetings to all Chinese workers and workers in
the rest of the world here today, on the eve of International
Labor Day.
</P>
<P>
Hu Jintao, a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee,
and of the Secretariat of the CPC Central Committee, extended the
greetings in a meeting today in the Great Hall of the People with
representatives of the country's Ten Excellent Workers and Labor Day
medalists.
</P>
<P>
Heroic collectives and role models of the working class have
been emerging in large numbers over the past 10-odd years. Those
cited this time are outstanding examples of them. "That you have
made glorious achievements at ordinary posts indicates vividly
that the working class is worthy of the title of our leading
class, and the major force in the reform and opening-up drive," Hu
noted, adding that the Party's guiding principle of wholeheartedly
relying on the working class has proven to be correct.
</P>
<P>
