<HEADLINE> China's Top Legislature Schedules Meeting for May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The Standing Committee of the
Eighth National People's Congress (NPC), the country's top
legislature, will convene its 25th meeting here May 6-10,
according to a meeting of the Standing Committee's chairman and
vice-chairpersons here today.
</P>
<P>
Today's meeting heard and passed a report of opinions on the
draft agenda and time schedule of the 25th meeting of the NPC
Standing Committee, which was delivered by Cao Zhi,
secretary-general of the NPC Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
The 25th meeting is expected to examine a number of draft laws
and motions, including the draft Administrative Supervision Law,
the draft Blood Donation Law, the motion on the quota allocation
of ethnic-minority deputies to the Ninth National People's
Congress, among others.
</P>
<P>
The agenda of the scheduled meeting may also include hearing
and examining a State Council report on work of poverty relief and
examining a written report of Chairman of the NPC Standing
Committee Qiao Shi's visit to France, Norway, Italy and Mongolia.
</P>
<P>
Today's meeting was presided over by Qiao Shi and attended by
ten vice-chairpersons, including Tian Jiyun, Wang Hanbin and Chen
Muhua. 
</P>
</TEXT>
