<HEADLINE> Singapore Increases Cooperation with Dalian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, April 29 (Xinhua) -- A Singaporean economic group,
which arrived here Monday night has shown interest in cooperation
with this coastal city in north China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The group, composed of 36 representatives from the Chan
Brother Group, Lin Teck Lee Group of Companies and some other
enterprises, held talks this morning with their local counterparts.
</P>
<P>
Loh Wing Siew, managing director of the Singapore Keppel
Corporation, Ltd, held business talks with four local companies in
succession. "Dalian is a famous port, and a modern city," he
said. "Its shipbuilding and repair work holds an important
position in China."
</P>
<P>
Loh, new to the city, has begun to collect information and
decided to make further contacts with some enterprises here,
hoping for similar cooperation to that his company has already
enjoyed in Suzhou, Shanghai, Guangdong and Yunnan.
</P>
<P>
Trade and economic cooperation between Singapore and Dalian are
doing well. Lee Kuan Yew, senior minister of Singapore, has
visited the city twice, and this has helped greatly promote the
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Singapore has opened 143 projects in Dalian, with 780 million
US dollars in investment, of which the co-funded Dayaowan
Container Dock Co., Ltd, now under construction, accounts for 480
million US dollars, said Wang Yanhui, deputy director of the
city's foreign trade and economic cooperation commission.
</P>
<P>
The group is expected to leave for east China's Jiangsu
Province in the next few days.  
</P>
</TEXT>
