<HEADLINE> "Overseas Journalists Welcome to Cover HK's Return" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Overseas journalists are welcome
to cover the planned activities to mark China's resumption of the
exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong, a leading official of the
Information Office of the State Council, announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The activities, scheduled for around the July 1 return of Hong
Kong to the embrace of the motherland, will take place in Beijing,
Shanghai, Tianjin, Chongqing, Guangzhou, Shenzhen and some other
places, according to the official.
</P>
<P>
Journalists from Hong Kong and Macao wishing to cover the
activities can file applications with the press center, which is
based in Beijing, and through the Hong Kong and Macao branches of
the Xinhua News Agency. Those from Taiwan can apply to the
Taiwan Affairs Office of the State Council, the official said.
</P>
<P>
Foreign journalists can apply to the press center via Chinese
embassies and consulates in other countries, the Hong Kong and
Macao branches of Xinhua News Agency, or the Hong Kong and Macao
visa offices of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs.
</P>
<P>
Overseas correspondents resident in Beijing can directly apply
to the press center, the official said.
</P>
<P>
While applying to cover the activities, journalists from Hong
Kong and Macao and foreign journalists must present credentials
from the news organizations they represent or other credentials
verifying their status as journalists or photo journalists, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The application period is May 1-31.  
</P>
</TEXT>
