<DOCNO> XIE19970429.0099 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-29 13:15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iranian Government Called to End Dialog With EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The Iranian parliament today
issued a strongly-worded statement calling on its government to
end dialog with the European Union (EU) member countries.
</P>
<P>
This is the latest response by the Iranian parliament to the
EU action taken after the Berlin court verdict which implicated
Iranian leaders behind the assassination of four Kurdish
opposition leaders in Mykonos restaurant in 1992.
</P>
<P>
The April 10 Berlin court verdict sparked a fierce diplomatic
battle between Iran and Germany.
</P>
<P>
The statement asked the EU countries to arrest and hand over
Iran's anti-government activists in European countries.
</P>
<P>
It accused the EU of supporting Iran's anti-government group
called the People's Mujahedeen Organization of Iran (PMOI) which
is based inside the Iraqi territory.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, it added, the readiness of the EU to condemn
terrorism and cooperate jointly to fight terrorism without any
exception should be taken as the criteria for the relations
between Iran and the EU countries.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian parliament then charged European countries of
exporting weapons of mass destruction to the sensitive region of
the Middle East and the Persian Gulf.
</P>
<P>
It termed such export as "violation of international
regulations and conventions" and as "an agent of instability in
the region."
</P>
<P>
The parliament said that the export of weapons of mass
destruction by some of the European countries during the
Iran-Iraq war (1980-88) caused damages amounting to billions of
dollars as well as the loss of thousands of Iranian lives.
</P>
<P>
The parliament said the Iran-EU dialog lacks constructiveness
and good intentions. "Therefore, we call on the government of the
Islamic Republic of Iran to end such dialog until the conditions
are realized," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Iran and Germany had recalled their ambassadors and expelled
four diplomats from each side after the verdict. All EU member
countries, except Greece, have recalled their ambassadors in a
protest against the involvement of Iranian leaders in the
Mykonos case.
</P>
<P>
All foreign ministers of EU member countries are going to
meet and iron out a joint and unified policy toward Iran at the
ministerial meeting Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
