<HEADLINE> FM Spokesman on Diaoyu Islands Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- China has always held that the
Diaoyu Islands issue would be settled through negotiation on the
basis of respecting facts when the time is ripe, Foreign Ministry
spokesman Cui Tiankai said here today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman reiterated that the Diaoyu islands and adjacent
islands have been an integral part of China's territories since
ancient times and that China's stand on this issue is clear-cut
and consistent.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman made the statement at a routine press conference,
when asked to comment on the report that a Japanese leader openly
claimed that the Diaoyu Islands are Japan's territories, and that
it is not necessary for Japan to hold consultations with any other
countries on the issue and the report that a member of Japan's
Diet and a reporter from Japan's Sankei Shimbun recently stepped
onto the Islands.
</P>
<P>
He said that there are disputes on this issue between the two
countries due to their different points of views and that this is
a undeniable fact.
</P>
<P>
"We have noticed a Japanese Deputy Chief Cabinet Secretary
expressed the view that the landing on the islands goes against
the policies of the Japanese government," he noted, "We demand
that the Japanese government take measures to prevent the repeat
of any infringement upon China's sovereignty and damage to
Sino-Japanese relations." 
</P>
</TEXT>
