<DOCNO> XIE19970429.0101 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK External Trade Value on Increase in March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The value of Hong Kong's total
exports in March 1997 increased 9.1 percent over a year earlier to
105.5 billion HK dollars (13.61 billion U.S. dollars), according
to the Census and Statistics Department.
</P>
<P>
Within total exports, the value of re-exports increased 10.2
percent to 90.7 billion HK dollars (11.7 billion U.S. dollars)
while the value of domestic exports increased 2.9 percent to 14.8
billion HK dollars (1.9 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The value of imports increased 6.0 percent in March this year
over a year earlier to 128.1 billion HK dollars (16.5 billion U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the department said that in March the value of
Hong Kong's re-exports showed a notable increase over a year
earlier while domestic exports rose modestly. The value of
imports continued to rise on a year-on-year basis.
</P>
<P>
In the first quarter of 1997, the value of total exports
increased 2.2 percent over the same quarter last year.
</P>
<P>
Among this, the value of re-export rose 3.7 percent while that
of domestic exports decreased 6.1 percent. The value of imports
showed an increase of 4.3 percent for the same period.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, as the value of total exports in
the first three months of 1997 was smaller than that of total
imports, a visible trade deficit of 48.2 billion HK dollars (6.22
billion U.S. dollars) was recorded. This was larger than the
deficit of 39.8 billion HK dollars (5.14 billion U.S. dollars)
recorded in the first quarter of 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
