<HEADLINE> Macao Inflation Rate Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Macao's inflation rate dropped to
4.6 percent in the first two months of this year, latest
statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics Department
today show that the composite consumer price index (CCPI) rose 4.6
percent based on the 12-month period from February, marking a
continuous drop in the inflation rate since late 1995.
</P>
<P>
Month by month, the CCPI rose 1.1 percent in February from
January, mainly due to price hikes in cereal and soft-drinks,
housing and service sectors.
</P>
<P>
The inflation rate declined to 4.8 percent in 1996, compared
with 8.6 percent in 1995.  
</P>
