<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Abolish Use of ODS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia is ready to implement
the international program on the abolishment of the use of ozone
depleting substances (ODS) by the end of this year, an official
said here today.
</P>
<P>
To that end, a number of domestic industries are ready for the
mass production of non-ODS refrigerating appliances, Sutamihardja,
an official from the Environment Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Pursuant to the Montreal Protocol which regulates the
abolishment of the use of ODS such as chloro fluoro carbon (CFC)
and its derivatives, developing countries including Indonesia
should stop import and use of CFC by the end of this year, said
the official.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, old appliances which are still using CFC in
Indonesia are allowed to continue to use that refrigerant until
the stock is exhausted, he added.
</P>
<P>
At present about 90 percent of the new appliances are using
non-ODS and the rest are special appliances whose CFC refrigerant
can not be replaced in a short time.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970429.0106 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-29 13:28 </DATE_TIME>
