for a three-day state visit to Turkey.
</P>
<P>
At the signing ceremony, Demirel said that as big states
in this region, Turkey and Romania would make full cooperation
for peace and stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
Turkey fully supports Romania for joining the European Union
(EU) and North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO), said Demirel.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish president said that Turkey and Romania decided
to make the Black Sea a sea of peace of cooperation,
adding that the two countries would continue the healthy
bilateral relations as well as the cooperation in the Black
Sea.
</P>
<P>
Turkey will provide assistance to Romania for its development
as there are 4,000 Turkish businessmen working in the country,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Demirel added that he accepted Constantinescu's invitation and
will realize his state visit to Romania in the shortest
time.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Constantinescu expressed his gratitude for
Turkey's full support for Romania's bid to EU and NATO full
membership.
</P>
<P>
He said that his official talks with Demirel were "most
productive and concrete", adding it is possible that the trade
volume between the two countries would surpass one billion
U.S. dollars in a short time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
