<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Full Foreign Ownership of Condominium Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The Thai cabinet today decided to
allow foreign investors to own 100 percent of a condominium
project in Thailand, making a stride toward the opening of the
country's property market.
</P>
<P>
The Thai cabinet today approved a draft bill on the matter
proposed by the Interior Ministry at its regular meeting, ending
long-standing speculations among investors.
</P>
<P>
According to the bill, foreigners will be allowed to buy
condominiums by withdrawing money from their accounts or
transferring from overseas baht accounts of other persons.
</P>
<P>
The Thai government's move is aimed at stimulating the sluggish
property market in the country, which plays an important role in
the country's economic performance.
</P>
<P>
Thailand currently follows a law on condominiums enacted in
1979 and amended in 1981, which allows foreigners to own a
condominium up to 40 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
