<HEADLINE> Monument Being Built for Construction Workers in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Work started here today on a
monument to construction worker Hu Yaolin and his 17-member team
that participated in the building of the Beijing Exhibition Hall
in 1954.
</P>
<P>
Hu Yaolin and his colleagues were designated a team of "shock
workers" when they were building the exhibition hall. Hu and all
his team mates were members of the Communist Youth League.
</P>
<P>
The team was formed to encourage creativity among young workers
and to speed up the construction of the building.
</P>
<P>
Zhan Baifa, deputy mayor of Beijing, attended the
ground-breaking ceremony for the monument. Zhan himself was once a
shock workers' team head, as was Li Ruihuan, chairman of the
national committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference.
</P>
<P>
Official sources say that Beijing now has about 2,000 shock
teams of construction workers.
</P>
<P>
This year is also the 43rd anniversary of the founding of such
teams, and a meeting was held here today to celebrate the event,
with Beijing Mayor Jia Qinglin attending.  
</P>
</TEXT>
