<HEADLINE> Chinese, Pakistani Presidents Hold Talks (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
held talks with President of the Islamic Republic of Pakistan
Farooq Ahmed Khan Leghari here today.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that mutual understanding, sympathy, trust and
support have become the outstanding features of Sino-Pakistani
ties. The bilateral friendship between the two countries has
withstood the test of time and been a model for relations between
countries with different social systems, he said.
</P>
<P>
Leghari arrived here this morning for a two-day working visit
at the invitation of President Jiang.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said it is a set policy of the Chinese government to
continue consolidating and developing the traditional
good-neighborly and mutually-beneficial friendship with Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
"We are ready to join our efforts with those of the Pakistan
people to carry the comprehensive cooperative partnership between
China and Pakistan into the 21st century," he said.
</P>
<P>
Expressing a heartfelt welcome to Leghari, Jiang said that he
still had fresh memories of his pleasant talks with President
Leghari during his visit to Pakistan at the latter's invitation
last year. He said Leghari has been an old friend of the Chinese
people since he visited China as president of Pakistan in
1994. Leghari's current China trip will further deepen the
bilateral friendly cooperative relations, he said.
</P>
<P>
Leghari cited Jiang's visit to Pakistan last year as an event
of great significance in the bilateral relations, and said that
the two countries will see their friendship continue to grow in
coming generations.
</P>
<P>
Noting that China and Pakistan are close friends and neighbors
whose two peoples share a long tradition of friendship, Jiang said
the bilateral relations have been growing soundly and smoothly
since the two countries forged diplomatic ties several decades
ago. Cooperation in the fields of politics, science, technology
and culture have kept growing and coordination in international
affairs has been close and consistent, he added.
</P>
<P>
President Leghari said the further strengthening of bilateral
ties is of strategic significance for both countries, and that
Pakistan will always remember that China has offered valuable
assistance to it in the past. Pakistan will, as always, continue
to devote every effort to supporting China's correct stand on the
issues of Taiwan, Hong Kong, Tibet and human rights, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
