<HEADLINE> Chinese, Pakistani Presidents Hold Talks (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Appreciating highly of the importance the Pakistani government
attaches to promotion of China-Pakistan relations, Jiang expressed
thanks for its consistent support for China on the issues of
Taiwan, Tibet and human rights.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, he said, the bilateral economic and trade
relations of cooperation have been strengthened, with the fields
expanded, forms diversified and results fruitful.
</P>
<P>
Jiang went on to say that he hoped the relevant departments of
the two sides would increase their exchanges and explore new ways
to further bilateral cooperation in the economic and trade field.
</P>
<P>
He suggested that the two sides join hands in more small and
medium-sized projects which yield quick profits, and conduct
multi-form cooperation in fields of economy, technology, trade and
investment.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president expressed the belief that through joint
efforts by the two governments and relevant corporations,
China-Pakistan economic and trade cooperation would see steady
advancement.
</P>
<P>
Leghari said the bilateral economic and trade cooperation has
scored effective progress and there is still huge potential.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan is willing to explore new ways and forms to expand
cooperation with China, he added.
</P>
<P>
During the talks the two presidents also conferred on
international and regional issues of common concern, and realized
much common ground.
</P>
<P>
