<HEADLINE> Yokthai Retains WBA Bantamweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Yokthai Sith Oar of Thailand
retained his World Boxing Association (WBA) junior bantamweight
title by drawing with Japanese challenger Satoshi Iida in Nagoya
of Japan on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
South Korean judge Park Dong An scored the fight 115-115 and
Oswaldo Sanchez of Venezuela had it 114-114. The third judge,
Manuel Rodriguez of Colombia, gave the fight to Iida 116-113 but
under the bout's rules two judges needed to agree on a winner.
</P>
<P>
It was Yokthai's third defensive title, which the 22-year-old
Thai grabbed from Alimi Goitia of Venezuela with a knock-out last
August. 
