<HEADLINE> 6 People Poisoned in Fire in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Six people were poisoned today
from smoke after a fire broke out in a chemical factory in
Istanbul, the largest city of Turkey, the semi-official Anatolia
News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that the fire, which broke out at 11:30 local
time (08:30 GMT) in Pendik Seyhli Village of Istanbul,
completely destroyed the Matsan Cosmetic Production Industry
Factory.
</P>
<P>
It said that flames are still spreading to new places and are
rising to 20 and 30 meters high. It is possible that new
explosions would occur.
</P>
<P>
The five workers and one citizen who were poisoned were rushed
to Kartal State Hospital for treatment.
</P>
<P>
Due to the danger of new explosions, the traffic had been
closed to the buildings, schools and working places within the
area of one square kilometer.
</P>
<P>
Turkish ganderme forces have taken large-scale security
measures in the region and reporters are not allowed to go to
the area of the incident for covering news stories, said the
agency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
