<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.N. Bodies Condemns Abduction of Children in Zaire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Children's Fund
(UNICEF) and the United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees
(UNHCR) today condemned the abduction of about 50 children from a
Zaire hospital in Lwiro, about 30 kilometers north of Bukavu near
the Rwandan border.
</P>
<P>
According to UNICEF and UNHCR reports on April 26, about 20
armed men, allegedly rebels from the AFDL (the Alliance of
Democratic Forces for the Liberation of Congo-Zaire), forcibly
took the Rwandan refugee children, who were under treatment, away
from the hospital in a truck.
</P>
<P>
A number of adults, believed to be parents or guardians of the
children, were also abducted, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The children have not been seen since and their whereabouts is
unknown.
</P>
<P>
The UNICEF said it was seriously concerned about the fate of
the children because most were in very poor condition and their
chances of survival without hospital treatment were slim.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. High Commissioner for Refugees also condemned the
abduction and demanded quick return of the children and adults.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
