<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The Lanzhou zoo in northwest
China's Gansu Province recently welcomed the arrivals of two
new "citizens", a snub-nosed monkey cub and an addax baby.
</P>
<P>
They were the seventh snub-nosed monkey and the 25th addax born
at the zoo, which has more than 1,000 wild animals of 100
different species.
</P>
<P>
