<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Rise Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Market endorsement of BHP Co.
Ltd's steel division overhaul led the Australian share market
higher today.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark all ordinaries index closed 17.4 points higher at
2479.1 with BHP 48.5 cents higher.
</P>
<P>
BHP, the market bellwether, announced a major restructuring of
its steel division, including the cutting of 2,000 jobs by 1999
with the closure of its Newcastle steelworks.
</P>
<P>
"Out of the 17 points on the upside of the all ordinaries, you
would have to attribute ten points of that to BHP," Peter Struk
from Reynolds and Co. said.
</P>
<P>
Brokers said the strength in BHP, which rose 2.79 percent,
dragged up other resource stocks.
</P>
<P>
The all resources index closed 16.1 points, or 1.17 percent,
higher at 1388.2, while the all industrials index ended 20.5
points up at 3894.8.
</P>
<P>
The banking sector also improved, rising 29.8 points to 4320.9,
National Australia Bank lifted 22 cents, Commonwealth Bank was 16
cents better, Westpac Bank was unchanged and ANZ rose three cents.
</P>
<P>
National turnover totaled 319.6 million shares traded, worth
881.28 million Australian dollars (682.9 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
</TEXT>
