<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rice Harvest in Vietnam Pushes Down Prices: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 29 (Xinhua) -- A senior Vietnamese official has
said that the rice harvest in Vietnam this year has a big negative
effect on prices of rice.
</P>
<P>
The bumper harvest of the winter-spring rice in Mekong delta
provinces in southern Vietnam is not only negatively affecting
farmers' lives but threatening the stability and sustainable
development of agricultural production and future national food
security, said Nguyen Cong Tan, agriculture and rural development
minister.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that 4.5 million tons of paddy rice are
stockpiled in the Mekong river delta provinces.
</P>
<P>
The harvest in the south resulted in a 2.8 percent fall in food
prices between March and April, according to official statistics.
The harvest season in the north is coming.
</P>
<P>
The government has urged state-owned food companies to buy
paddy rice at the government's recommended price from farmers'
stock in the Mekong river delta provinces. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
