Hu, also member of the Secretariat of the CPC Central
Committee, said that since the normalization of the diplomatic
relations between the two countries, the bilateral cooperation in
all fields has been expanding.
</P>
<P>
Various levels of friendly contacts have witnessed obvious
increases, leaders of the countries have maintained contacts and
dialogue, and the Sino-Japanese friendly relations have enjoyed
great development, Hu said.
</P>
<P>
Hu elaborated that both sides should treasure this hard-won
achievement and, with a view to the future, promote the friendly
Sino-Japanese ties in a long-term, healthy and steady way that is
oriented towards the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Hu stressed that it is the historical responsibility of the
younger generations to inherit and explore the cause of friendship
that was initiated by the elder generations of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Hu went on to say, the young generations should be instructed
to have a proper understanding of and a correct approach to
history.
</P>
<P>
Hu urged further strengthening the friendly exchanges between
the young generations, increasing mutual understanding and trust,
making concerted efforts to promote the friendship and cooperation
between the two peoples and contributing more to the progress of
the bilateral good neighborliness.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Hu also briefed the Japanese visitors on
China's reform and opening up.
</P>
<P>
Katsuya Okada said his party attaches great importance to its
friendly exchanges with the Chinese Communist Party.
</P>
<P>
The Japan-China relation is an important part of Japan's
external ties, and the younger generation of statesmen of Japan
should further enhance the contacts with China and take a positive
attitude in promoting the steady advancement of the bilateral
relations.
</P>
<P>
Li Shuzheng, Head of the International Department of the CPC
Central Committee, was present at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese visitors arrived in China on April 26 as guests of
the international department.  
</P>
</TEXT>
