<DOCNO> XIE19970429.0147 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Maintains Steady Growth in Machine-Building Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- China kept steady and appropriate
growth in the machine-building industry which generated 111.29
billion yuan of output value in the first quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
This represents a rise of 9.3 percent over the same period of
last year, according to the Ministry of Machine-Building Industry.
</P>
<P>
The ministry also disclosed that the machine-building
industrial sector sold 104.81 million worth of commodities
manufactured from January to March, a rise of 7.6 percent over the
same period of 1996, and the ratio of production to marketing
stood at 94.2 percent in the first quarter of the year, 2.5
percentage points higher than last year.
</P>
<P>
The sector delivered 6.43 billion yuan worth of commodities for
exports, an increase of 8.3 percent over last year, said official
sources.
</P>
<P>
An official with the ministry warned that the sector has not
shown marked improvement in economic benefits and much still waits
to be done.
</P>
<P>
Out of the ten major businesses, only automobile, meters and
instruments, and petrochemical, businesses are making profits, the
rest are money losers.
</P>
<P>
The reasons behind the slow improvement of economic efficiency
were explained as the continuous implementation of the
comparatively tight money policy, a continued control over
investment in fixed assets, and the state's continued control over
the issues of money.
</P>
<P>
The official pledged that the Ministry of Machine-Building
Industry will continue to intensify reform and will strive to
bring the sector to healthy development in the upcoming three to
five years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
