<HEADLINE> Zambia Withdraws Ambassador From War-torn Zaire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Zambia has evacuated from Zaire's
capital Kinshasa its ambassador, Ian Sikazwe.
</P>
<P>
Local newspaper Zambia Daily Mail today quoted Foreign
Minister Lawrence Shimba as saying on Monday that the action was
taken because of the volatile situation in Zaire.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that his country will not interfere in the
internal affairs of Zaire and was compelled to recall all its
diplomats until the situation improves.
</P>
<P>
He said the consulate of Zambia in Lubumbashi, the second
largest city of Zaire, has been non-operational following the
return of the consular-general and his staff with their families.
</P>
<P>
"We have recalled our ambassador from Kinshasa just as we had
recalled our consular-general from Lubumbashi because we do not
want to take sides in the ongoing conflict there," said Shimba.
</P>
<P>
The anti-government forces led by Laurent Kabila are advancing
on Kinshasa following the seizure of Lubumbashi earlier this
month. 
</P>
