<HEADLINE> Share Prices Fall Further on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to fall
lower on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index declined another 6.59 points to close at 1990.2
points today.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume was still thin at 100.99 million units,
worth 315.25 million Singapore dollars (about 218.92 million U.S.
dollars). Declines continued to overwhelm advances by 241 to 65,
while 314 other counters remained steady.
</P>
<P>
The Kuala Lumpur Ind. was the most actively traded stock as it
posted a turnover of 6.99 million units. It was followed by the
Singapore Telecom which had 6.62 million of shares traded. The
Hong Kong Land was next with 3.78 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Local beverage and food maker F&AMP;N led the gainers of the day as
it rose 40 cents to finish at 10.5 Singapore dollars. Elec
increased 25 cents to close at 5.65 US dollars, while JMH 400 and
the Overseas Chinese Banking Corporation (OCBC) Foreign ended 20
cents higher each at 5.5 U.S. dollars and 16.6 Singapore dollars
respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 was the biggest loser as it
declined 1.5 Singapore dollars to close at 20 Singapore dollars.
City Developments warrant 98 fell 85 cents to end at 8.8 Singapore
dollars, while Diversified Resources was 62 cents lower at 3.42
dollars.  
</P>
