<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Singapore Emphasize Long-term, Overall Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin and
visiting Singaporean Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong emphasized today
that China and Singapore should look forward to the future and
establish long-term and comprehensive bilateral co-operation.
</P>
<P>
Co-operation between the two countries in various fields are
undergoing healthy improvement, their coordination in world and
regional issues have been sound, and their consensus expanding,
the Chinese President said.
</P>
<P>
"China and Singapore should join their hands more closely so as
to establish a kind of good-neighborliness facing the 21st century
based on mutual trust," he said.
</P>
<P>
Goh agreed that both sides should continue to push forward the
bilateral friendly co-operation.
</P>
<P>
China will soon resume its exercise of sovereignty over Hong
Kong, Jiang said, adding China will steadfastly stick to the "one
country, two systems" policy and "Hong Kong people governing Hong
Kong" and "high autonomy of Hong Kong" so as to maintain the
prosperity and stability of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Singapore is full of confidence over the future of Hong Kong,
and will continue its investment there, Goh said.
</P>
<P>
After the return of Hong Kong, the issue of Macao will be
settled and the reunification of the two sides across the Taiwan
straits will also be realized, Jiang said, adding that this
accords with the will of the people and the general trend of
events, and can not be held back by anyone or any force.
</P>
<P>
Jiang reiterated that China is an important force in
safeguarding world peace, stability, and prosperity, and will
never constitute any threat to any other countries.
</P>
<P>
The President pointed out that the world is moving towards
multi-polarity even as the global situation tends towards
relaxation. China is willing to increase its co-operation with the
world's countries based on equality and mutual-benefit, and will
continue to exert efforts for a peaceful and stable international
pattern, he said.
</P>
<P>
China stresses its co-operation with neighboring countries, and
is willing to contribute more to the regional peace and stability
together with Singapore, he added.
</P>
<P>
Responding to Goh's remark that the ASEAN will actively promote
its ties with China, Jiang expressed his pleasure over the
progress of Sino-ASEAN ties over the past years, saying to improve
relationship with ASEAN is an important part of China's foreign
policy.
</P>
<P>
Goh conveyed to Jiang the good wishes and cordial regards of
Singaporean President Ong Teng Cheong and senior minister Lee Kuan
Yew, and Jiang asked Goh to convey his cordial regards and good
wishes to President Ong Teng Cheong and senior minister Lee Kuan
Yew upon his return home.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
