<HEADLINE> Baotou Recovers Quickly from Earthquake (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This year the city will build 120,000 square meters of houses
for schools and hospitals. As for urban construction, all water
and gas supply facilities, bridges and roads are expected to go
into normal operation.
</P>
<P>
As for infrastructure construction, the city has invested 80
million yuan in repairing water, heat and gas supply pipelines,
which has basically guaranteed the city's normal life order. The
city has also purchased 186 sets of equipment and repaired 154 for
industrial production.
</P>
<P>
The city is also obliged to revamp schoolrooms on a large scale
ten years ahead of schedule, Zhao said.
</P>
<P>
But Zhao also acknowledged that the rebuilding is still facing
financial difficulties. Water and gas supplies are difficult to
reach so many new apartments. In factories, equipment are waiting
for repair.
</P>
<P>
The city will strive to finish the reconstruction task by the
end of this year, the vice mayor said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the city's Gross Domestic Product (GDP) is expected to
reach 21.5 billion yuan, up 20 percent over the previous year,
while financial revenue will strive to reach 2.4 billion yuan, up
10 percent.  
</P>
