<HEADLINE> 3 Injured in Clash In Sri Lanka's Kelaniya University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Three students were seriously
injured today in a clash among students in Kelaniya University in
Western province of Sri Lanka, according to police sources here.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that a free for all at the Kelaniya University
between two groups of students was quelled by armed police in the
early hours today.
</P>
<P>
The trouble started around 01:30 and ended at 04:30 with three
students seriously injured and admitted to hospital.
</P>
<P>
They said that the clash broke out when a group of students
attempted to paste posters in the campus premises at night.
Students who were in the halls of residence were notified of the
attempt and protested.
</P>
<P>
Then, the sources said, stones, bricks and sticks were used in
the fight which spread to all sections of the campus.
</P>
<P>
Police believed that a group of students belonging to a
political party attempted to paste the posters which were in
connection with the forthcoming May Day.
</P>
<P>
Armed police took up positions around the campus to prevent any
further clash. A special team of policemen was due to question
several students, the sources added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
