<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Senior CPC Official Meets Japanese Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- A senior official of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) today called for joint efforts to
push forward the Sino-Japanese friendship into the new century.
</P>
<P>
"This will be the best commemoration for the upcoming 25th
anniversary of the normalization of Sino-Japanese diplomatic
relations." said Hu Jintao, member the Standing Committee of the
Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central
Committee, at a meeting with a delegation of the Liberal
Democratic Party (LDP) of Japan led by Yamazaki Taku, chairman of
the party's Political Affairs Investigation Committee.
</P>
<P>
Hu, also a member of the Secretariat of the CPC Central
Committee, said: "the present Sino-Japanese friendship, forged
through efforts of generations, should be treasured by all of us."
</P>
<P>
"Historical experience, positive or negative, has proved that
the friendship between China and Japan benefits the two peoples as
well as the cause of peace and progress of humanity." he noted,
adding that "past experience, if not forgotten, would be a guide
for the future."
</P>
<P>
He emphasized that both Chinese and Japanese statesmen should
bear in mind historical lessons and seek common understanding to
enhance the good-neighborly relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Appreciating the LDP's positive attitude towards China and its
relations with the CPC, Hu said that the CPC is ready to increase
exchanges and cooperation with the LDP on the basis of
independence, full equality, mutual respect, and mutual
non-interference in each other's internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
Hu added that the CPC hopes to work with the LDP for
establishing and developing a long-term, sound and stable
Sino-Japanese relations.
</P>
<P>
Hu also briefed the visitors on China's present domestic
political and economic situations.
</P>
<P>
Yamazaki said that the LDP attaches great importance to
developing its ties with the CPC and hopes to further strengthen
these ties.
</P>
<P>
"Our current visit to China on the eve of the 25th anniversary
aims to help promote bilateral friendly relations through
exchanges and cooperation between the two parties." he noted.
</P>
<P>
Yamazaki and his party arrived here Sunday as guests of the
CPC.  
</P>
</TEXT>
