<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Earth Experiences Constant Changes in Climate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Chinese glaciologists discovered
after three years research that the earth has witnessed constant
climate changes, big and small, through different periods of
history.
</P>
<P>
Yao Tandong, a researcher at the Lanzhou-based Institute of
Glaciology and Cryopedology attached to the Chinese Academy of
Sciences, said the discovery made by him and his colleagues was
based on researches of records of glaciers at the Qinghai-Tibet
Plateau.
</P>
<P>
He said, according to their analysis, since 1570, the climate
of earth experienced several marked changes.
</P>
<P>
He added that the 17th and 19th centuries were relatively cold
periods with less rainfalls while the 18th and 20th century were
relatively warm periods with more rainfalls.
</P>
<P>
They believed that the changes are far more complicated than
the transition of the four seasons in a year.
</P>
<P>
Yao said each cold or warm period contains shorter cold or warm
periods. For instance, the 16th century was a warm period,
however, by the end of that century, the temperature on earth
dropped gradually and reached the cold peak by the mid-17th
century.
</P>
<P>
He added that the temperature picked up rapidly at the
beginning of the 18th century, dropped sharply at the beginning of
the 19th century and resumed to the normal level at the beginning
of the 20th century.
</P>
<P>
Yao said the changes in the climate could also be proved by the
records of the amount of precipitation. During the warm 18th
century, the average annual precipitation amount reached above 210
mm, while the colder 19th century witnessed an annual precipitation
amount averaging 180 mm.
</P>
<P>
So far, scientists have not found the cause of the constant
great changes in the earth climate. They guess that the changes in
the earth climate is closely related to the angles of the
Sun's radiation and with sun spots. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970429.0188 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
