<HEADLINE> Qian, Albright Hold Talks on Sino-U.S. Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice Premier and
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen today held talks with U.S. Secretary
of State Madeleine Albright on Sino-U.S. relations.
</P>
<P>
The two foreign ministers reviewed the progress the two
countries had made since the beginning of this year and agreed to
further improve and develop the Sino-U.S relationship, Chinese
Foreign Ministry spokesman Shen Guofang said at a press
conference.
</P>
<P>
Qian said in the talks that more and more people have seen the
importance of the Sino-U.S. relationship, which will have
significant influence on the world pattern in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Qian described Albright' February visit to China as successful
and said it made a good beginning for this year's continuing
development of the relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that he hoped his visit to Washington would keep and
strengthen the momentum of dialogue at the high level so that the
relationship could be further developed.
</P>
<P>
Albright agreed with Qian, saying that the U.S. people are
convinced that the Sino-U.S. relationship is one of the most
important bilateral relationships, Shen Guofang said.
</P>
<P>
