<HEADLINE> Beijing's Exports Up Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Recent statistics from Beijing's
foreign trade and economic cooperation commission show its exports
in the first three months up slightly, at 3.6 percent more than
for the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The capital's foreign trade is maintaining steady growth, with
703 million US dollars worth of foreign trade, including 234
million in imports and 470 million in exports.
</P>
<P>
The commission said that the increase in exports from last
year's drop came from joint-ventures. In the January-March period,
exports of joint ventures reached 180 million US dollars worth, up
51.3 percent from the same period last year, and accounting for
38.4 percent of the city's total.
</P>
<P>
The processing trade also had an export increase. Its export in
value accounted for 55.9 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
Machinery and electronic products are the major export items of
joint ventures.
</P>
<P>
The city plans to export 2.3 billion US dollars worth of goods
this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
