<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Export Trade Booms In Guangxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Statistics from Guangxi
Department of Foreign Trade and Economy Co-operation has shown
that the region's import and export volumes reached 460 million US
dollars for the first quarter of 1997, 4.7 percent higher over the
same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The 370 million US dollars of exports and 90 million US dollars
of imports were 2 percent and 18 percent higher over the same
period of 1996, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Exports kept falling during the January-October period of 1996,
so the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Regional Government took measures
to end this situation earlier this year. Governments at all levels
are speeding up the tax refund process to reduce enterprises'
burdens.
</P>
<P>
The year 1997 has seen an increase of eleven enterprises
gaining export rights. The border export trade in the first
quarter increased by 21.5 percent over the same period of last
year.
</P>
<P>
With the lowering of loan rates, the rate of Renminbi has kept
steady while the prices keep falling. These have contributed
to lowering export costs and expanding export. 
</P>
</TEXT>
