<HEADLINE> Japanese PM to Visit NZ </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Japanese Prime Minister
Ryutaro Hashimoto will arrive here late tonight to start a one-day
visit to New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
NZ officials expect the visit to reinforce the growing
partnership between the two countries in all spheres and the
personal relationship between Hashimoto and his NZ counterpart Jim
Bolger.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders are scheduled to hold a meeting tomorrow
morning and have a bush walk in the afternoon.
</P>
<P>
However, a statement released from the Foreign Ministry this
evening said the scheduled meetings Hashimoto to have with Deputy
Prime Minister Winston Peters and the Opposition leader Helen
Clark have been canceled.
</P>
<P>
The cancellation was "due to the fact that Prime Minister
Hashimoto's itinerary in Wellington had to be modified to be as
light as possible, as a result of fatigue from his long journey,
and the Peruvian hostage incident immediately prior to his
departure from Japan," according to the statement.
</P>
<P>
Relations between Japan and New Zealand are good with no major
problems in any field. Japan is New Zealand's second largest
trading partner after Australia and an important source of
tourists.  
