<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand share market
rebounded today after opening firmer following a solid showing on
Wall Street overnight.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended 9 points higher at 2249 with a turnover
of nearly 61 million NZ dollars (41 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Forestry stocks were in high demand and saw heavy buying.
Carter Holt Harvey shares rose 3 cents to 320 cents and Fletcher
Paper gained 3 cents to 309 cents.
</P>
<P>
Other leaders to gain included Telecom, up 2 cents to 645 cents
and Air New Zealand, up 1 cent to 285 cents. However, Brierley
Investment remained unchanged at 126 cents.
</P>
<P>
Lion Nathan was the only loser among the major leaders, whose
shares shed 1 cent to 341 cents after the company released a lower
interim profit.
</P>
<P>
There were 43 rises and 42 falls overall.  
