<HEADLINE> India-Sri Lanka Business Meeting to Be Held in Colombo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The fifth meeting of India-Sri
Lanka Joint Business Council (ISLJBC), which was set up in 1991,
will be opened in Colombo next month, according to official
sources here today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the meeting will discuss several
important issues concerning Indo-Sri Lankan bilateral trade. Among
them will investment policy, joint venture opportunities, tourism
and trade.
</P>
<P>
Imbalance in bilateral trade has been the principal concern of
the Sri Lankan side during the earlier four meetings of the
ISLJBC. Several steps have been contemplated to increase Sri
Lanka exports to India as an outcome of the earlier meetings, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
The sources added that a large number of Sri Lankan businessmen
have established new business links with their Indian counterparts
by attending the ISLJBC meetings.
</P>
<P>
The last ISLJBC meeting was held in Madras with the
participation of a large business delegation from Sri Lanka.
</P>
</TEXT>
