<HEADLINE> Sino-German Cooperation in Planting Trees Fruitful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, April 29 (Xinhua) -- A tree-planting project
between China and Germany has been turning north China's Hebei
province green since last year.
</P>
<P>
Since the Sino-German project started last April, nearly 21,000
ha. of trees have been planned in four counties. The province
reports that 2,219 ha. of trees have been planted and 2,883 ha. of
mountainous forest areas have been protected over the past year.
</P>
<P>
One million Deutsche marks have been provided by the KFW Bank
of Germany for the project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
