<HEADLINE> Albania Opens Airport for Multinational Force </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The Rinas International Airport in
Tirana was opened round the clock starting early this morning for
the need of the multinational force in Albania.
</P>
<P>
The country has been in a state of emergency and curfew imposed
since March 2. The airport was closed on March 13 and reopened
during the day from March 20 on.
</P>
<P>
Italian force reinstalled lighting equipment for the night
taking off and landing, fireproof and other supplementary
equipment for the wireless communications with airplanes.
</P>
<P>
The Rinas airport is the only international one in the European
country and it is under expansion contracted by German Siemens
Company.
</P>
<P>
Violence erupted in Albania and has lasted since March, killing
more than 200 people. The multinational force, which will reach
its full deployment of 6,000 next week, is responsible for
securing routes for humanitarian aid and restoring order to allow
parliamentary elections to be arranged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
