<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Establishes First Base of Space Seed Breeding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The China Aerospace
Corporation has established the first space seed base in Bazhou
City in Hebei Province, a major grain producer, to put crop seeds
on a retrievable satellite to study the influences of space.
</P>
<P>
The space seed breeding technology, developed in the 1990s in
China, Russia and the US, studies the effects of gravity and
vacuums on chemical bonds, free radicals, and DNA chromosomal
structures.
</P>
<P>
Tests in northeast China's Heilongjiang Province and other
places have shown that rice and wheat output can be increased
eight to 10 percent and vegetable output by 50 to 120 percent
using these techniques.
</P>
<P>
One expert says that planting 1.5 kilograms of space treated
green pepper seeds on one hectare of land will yield 6,750
kilograms of quality seeds.
</P>
<P>
The Bazhou base will bring wheat, sunflower, and grass seeds
from Canada and maize seeds from Hungary for space breeding.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
