<HEADLINE> UNESCO to Set Up 4th Representative Office In Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Educational,
Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO) signed an agreement
with the state authorities of Pernambuco, Brazil, today to set up
a representative office in the capital of this state.
</P>
<P>
The UNESCO representatives office, or the fourth of its kind in
Brazil, will begin operations at the end of May in Recife, the
capital of Pernambuco, a state in northeastern Brazil, where it
will cooperate with the mayor's office of that city in the sectors
of education, culture, health and the environment.
</P>
<P>
The accord was signed in Recife today by Brazilian
Vice-President Marco Maciel, Mayor of Recife Roberto Magalhaes and
Jorge Wertheim, the UNESCO representative in Brazil.
</P>
<P>
The vice-president reaffirmed that the presence of the UNESCO
will facilitate cooperation in important projects.
</P>
<P>
For his part, UNESCO representative Jorge Wertheim stressed
that the organization can help with exchanges in the tourist
sector with the Southern Common Market (Mercosur). 
</P>
</TEXT>
