<HEADLINE> State to Tighten Control over Items for Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The state is making special
preparations to supervise the quality of food and other articles
of daily use for children, today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the Central Committee of the Communist Youth
League of China and the State Bureau of Technical Supervision
(SBTS), state supervisors will focus on lactic acid beverages,
ice-creams, textbooks and clothes.
</P>
<P>
"With the theme of protecting our children, supervision will be
conducted by sampling product quality and responding to
questionnaires," said Qiao Baoping, an official in charge of
children's rights and interests.
</P>
<P>
"The quality of children's food and their articles for daily
use is closely related to their healthy growth and an issue of
concern for parents, teachers and society," the official said.
</P>
<P>
He said though many Chinese products for children have become
well-known brands, thanks to years of painstaking efforts in
quality control to enter the domestic market and produce harmful
effects in children's physical and psychological well being.
</P>
<P>
Samples gathered from producers around the country have been
completed, and sent to five state quality inspection centers,
said Xuan Xiang, an official with SBTS, which overseas quality
control work in China.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the central committee of the Communist Youth
League of China will arrange for the country's 400 million
youngsters to participate in the quality supervision process by
allowing them to express their complaints and opinions in
specially prepared questionnaires.
</P>
<P>
Results of the inspection and supervision will be publicized by
June, 1, International Children's Day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
