<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> One Dead, 17 Injured in Russia's Pyatigorsk Blast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 28 (Xinhua) -- An explosion in Pyatigorsk, a
Russian resort in Caucasus region, killed one and wounded 17 on
Monday, according to a report reaching here.
</P>
<P>
The explosion, which occurred at the railway station in the
city of Pyatigorsk, destroyed the roof, windows and doors and
damaged the building's structures.
</P>
<P>
Investigators are working at the site. It was alleged as a
terrorist action, but no charges have been brought against anyone
so far.
</P>
<P>
Russian Deputy Interior Minister Pyotr Latyshev has left for
Pyatigorsk along with the head of the anti-terrorist center Viktor
Zorin.
</P>
<P>
According to Itar-Tass news agency, Russian Interior Minister
Anatoly Kulikov directly pointed to a "Chechen trace" in the
explosion.
</P>
<P>
Two women suspected in the terrorist act have been detained,
Kulikov added.
</P>
<P>
Federal Security Service spokesman Alexander Zdanovich also
confirmed that "there are indications that the act involved
Chechen terrorists." 
</P>
</TEXT>
