<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy Adopts Action Plan to Protect Children's Rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The Italian government today
published an Action Plan for Children, under which children and
adolescents in the country will acquire new legal rights.
</P>
<P>
Social Solidarity Minister Divia Turco said that the plan
included revision of the penal code and judicial system, a reform
of the system of creches and day nurseries and also of laws on
adoption.
</P>
<P>
It also includes provision for experimentation with local
children's councils elected by children, to contribute to the
democratic process.
</P>
<P>
A bill to fight child poverty, refinance schemes for protecting
children at risk and improving leisure facilities, with spending
of some 800 billion lire (470 million U.S. dollars), is already in
the parliament.
</P>
<P>
Another bill will be tabled shortly to incorporate the Hague
convention on international adoption, Turco said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
