<HEADLINE> Panama Grants Asylum to Former Ecuadoran President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The Panamanian government
decided today to grant asylum to former Ecuadoran President Abdala
Bucaram, who is currently living as a refugee in this country.
</P>
<P>
Erich Auerbach, the spokesperson for the Panamanian Foreign
Ministry, said the Panamanian government responded favorably to
the request made by the former Ecuadoran President on March 18.
</P>
<P>
Asylum was also granted to Bucaram's wife Maria Rosa Pulley de
Bucaram and his children Jacobo, Linda, Abdala and Michelle
Bucaram Pulley.
</P>
<P>
This decision was made by Panamanian President Ernesto Perez
Balladares and Foreign Minister Ricardo Alberto Arias.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador's Congress voted this February to remove President
Abdala Bucaram, who was elected last October, for "mental
incapacity". 
