<HEADLINE> Job Agencies Becoming Popular in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Zhang Xiaoying, a young Chinese
worker, was all smiles as she walked out of the Golden Bridge Job
Agency in the capital of east China's Jiangxi Province.
</P>
<P>
Zhang had been idle at home for about half a year and was
apprehensive about the possibilities of landing a satisfactory job
very soon. But, she went to the job agency ten days ago to try her
luck.
</P>
<P>
Nanchang now has more than 60 agencies engaged in this kind of
work, that employee nearly 2,000 people. Some of the agencies are
owned by the state and some by individuals.
</P>
<P>
Over the past three years, the job agencies have provided
138,400 jobs for people and have become a major source of
employment for out-of-work people in the city.
</P>
<P>
There are now more than 160,000 idle workers in Nanchang,
according to an official with the Nanchang City Labor Bureau,
which is in change of administration of job agencies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
