<DOCNO> XIE19970429.0254 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Domestic Savings Rate Up in Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The domestic savings rate in Peru
climbed up from 16.9 percent of the gross domestic product (GDP)
in 1995 to 17.7 percent in 1996, said the country's Central
Reserve Bank (BCR) today.
</P>
<P>
A report released today by BCR said external savings dropped
from 7.3 percent of the GDP in 1995 to 5.8 percent in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The balance of payments improved with a decrease in the deficit
of 4.3 billion dollars in 1995 to 3.5 billion in 1996, said the
report.
</P>
<P>
The smaller deficit in the current account was due to a 442
million dollar decrease in interest payments of the external
public debt and to the 189 million dollar deficit in foreign
trade, it added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
