<HEADLINE> Echoes From The Mercosur (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, April 28 (Xinhua) --
</P>
<P>
SUCRE, BOLIVIA -- The Andean Community and the Southern Common
Market (Mercosur) declared on April 23 its "firm political will"
to create an extensive free trade zone.
</P>
<P>
The commitment was contained in a joint statement signed by
the presidents of Bolivia, Colombia, Ecuador and Venezuela, all
members of the Andean Pact and the president of Paraguay as the
pro tempore president of the Mercosur.
</P>
<P>
The Andean Community hopes that the final draft of the free
trade agreement will be ready this year. The Mercosur includes
Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay.
</P>
<P>
OTTAWA -- Canada is looking for a pact with the Mercosur before
the completion of a Free Trade Agreement of the Americas (FTAA),
Prime Minister Jean Chretien told Brazilian Presient Fernando
Henrique Cardoso.
</P>
<P>
Canada is showing an unusual interest in reaching an agreement
because "the Canadian economy fits in very well" with that
subregional bloc, pointed out the prime minister.
</P>
<P>
Cardoso said that an agreement between the Mercosur and
Canada would be a step towards the establishment of a FTAA by
the year 2005. Chretien and Cardoso met on April 22.
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- The building of the first high-voltage power
line that will carry electric power from Argentina to Chile across
the Andean Cordillera was awarded to the Chilgener Company.
</P>
<P>
The power line will transport energy from a combined-cycle
thermal plant that Chilgener will build in Salta, a province in
Argentina to Antofagasta, a region in Chile, where it will supply
electricity mainly to mining companies.
</P>
<P>
The power line between the Salta plant and the border will
require an investment of 50 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO -- Brazilian President Fernando Henrique
Cardos and Argentine President Carlos Menem signed an agreement
for military cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The agreement will link the armed forces of both countries but
"is not a military alliance", declared Menem in a meeting.
</P>
<P>
Cardoso and Menem met recently in Rio de Janeiro to talk
about trade disputes and to sign other agreements in
transportation and energy matters. (to be continued)

nnnn
05:04 05:04 g # NAB
nnnn
</P>
</TEXT>
