<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Australian newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
The Australian
</P>
<P>
-- Prime Minister John Howard plans to rush legislation into
Parliament next month to protect graziers and miners from native
title claims after winning yesterday the backing of all States and
Territories except Queensland for his 10-point response to the
High Court Wik decision.
</P>
<P>
The Sydney Morning Herald
</P>
<P>
-- Australian scientists have discovered that mice exposed to
electromagnetic radiation equivalent to spending one hour a day on
a digital mobile phone are twice as likely to develop lymphoma, a
cancer of the immune system.
</P>
<P>
The Australian Financial Review
</P>
<P>
-- The Reserve Bank of Australia has warned that union efforts
to seek flow-on wage rises through the award system could threaten
Australia's low inflation rate.  
</P>
